title: Thieves reportedly steal 1,600kg of gold in Canadian airport heist
description: A heist at a Canadian airport appears to have netted thieves an incredible haul of more than 1,630kg (around 1.6 tonnes) of gold - which has a value of about £84m ($104m).

title: The Pope, JK Rowling and Ant and Dec among hundreds of thousands losing their blue ticks as Twitter's cull begins
description: Twitter has finally started removing "legacy" blue ticks from verified accounts, with some of the world's best-known figures losing the verification sign.

title: Putin needs to be held accountable for kids being taken from Ukraine, US ambassador says
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin needs to be held accountable for the Ukrainian children who have been taken from their homeland, the US ambassador-at-large for global criminal justice has told Sky News.

title: Russian diplomat claims Ukrainian children moved to Russia are being 'saved' from war
description: Russia's deputy ambassador to the UN has denied his country is carrying out war crimes through the mass forcible transfers of children, and claims its army is in fact "saving" them.

title: Lift-off! Watch moment SpaceX launches world's most powerful rocket at second attempt
description: SpaceX has launched the biggest and most powerful rocket ever made in a landmark test - but it exploded minutes after taking flight.

title: Sexual offence charges against Madeleine McCann prime suspect dropped by German court
description: A German court has rejected a possible rape trial for the prime suspect in the disappearance of Madeleine McCann, Christian B.

title: 'We are here, we are here': Paris pension protesters call on Macron to resign
description: Hundreds of protesters in France briefly entered the offices of a stock market operator on Thursday as protests against President Macron's pension reform continued.

title: What NATO chief's high-risk visit to Ukraine means for the war
description: The sight of the head of NATO in Kyiv will send the clearest possible message to Moscow that the alliance stands fully behind Ukraine even though the nation is not – yet – a member state.

title: Climber rescued after surviving for days trapped on one of world's highest mountains
description: A climber has been rescued after plunging into a deep crack in one of the most dangerous mountains in the world.

title: Michael Schumacher's family plans legal action over AI 'interview'
description: Michael Schumacher's family are planning to take legal action against a German magazine which published an "interview" with the seven-time F1 champion generated by artificial intelligence.

title: Mysterious flash of light over Kyiv sparks alarm and confusion after NASA denies its satellite crashed
description: A mysterious flash of light that lit up the skies over Kyiv sparked alarm, confusion and speculation as to what may have caused it.

title: 'Mind-blowing' rare solar eclipse wows in Australia and Indonesia
description: Thousands of stargazers gathered in a remote Australian town to witness a "spectacular" rare solar eclipse.

title: 'Ruthless and calculating con-artist' jailed for trying to poison lookalike with cheesecake
description: A 'ruthless and calculating' woman has been jailed for 21 years for trying to kill her friend in the US with a poisoned cheesecake to steal her identity.
